removeOutgroups<-function(cover.matrix, outgroups){
  #remove outgroups
  rm.isolates = c(grep(paste(outgroups, collapse='|'),colnames(cover.matrix)))
  new.cover.matrix <- cover.matrix[,-rm.isolates]
  return(new.cover.matrix)
  }


calculateCoverage <- function(cover.matrix){
  #cover of the genes in reference genbank 
  gene.totals <- NULL
  for (i in seq(80,100,by = 5)){
    gene.totals <- cbind(gene.totals, apply(cover.matrix,1,function(x){sum(x>=i)}))
  }
  
  #create matrix for output
  core = matrix(NA, nrow = length(define.core), ncol = 5)
  colnames(core) = c("80%", "85%","90%","95%",'100%')
  
  # loop through the different cutoff values for the number of isolates with the different levels of gene cover
  define.core = seq(0.8,1.0,by = 0.01)
  for(i in 1:length(define.core)){
    # multiply by total number of isolates
    x = define.core[i]*ncol(cover.matrix)
    core[i,] = c(sum(gene.totals[,1] >= x), sum(gene.totals[,2] >= x),sum(gene.totals[,3] >= x),sum(gene.totals[,4] >= x),sum(gene.totals[,5] >= x))
    }
  core <- as.data.frame(core)
  core$percents <- define.core
  x=(melt(core, id=c("percents")))
  
  #plot results
  g=ggplot(x, aes(x=percents, y=value, colour=variable)) + geom_line() + ylab('Number of genes') + xlab('Percentage presence') + scale_color_discrete(name='Coverage of gene')
  
  return(list('core'=core,'gplot'=g))
}
siteConservation <- function(snp.table){
  num.present = apply(snp.table,1,function(x){sum(x %in% c("A","C","G","T"))})
  define.core = seq(0.75,1.0,by = 0.01)
  num.snps = NULL
  for(i in 1:length(define.core)){
    num.snps = c(num.snps, sum(num.present >= (ncol(snp.table)-1)*define.core[i]))
  }
  #print (cbind(num.snps,define.core))
  x=as.data.frame(cbind(num.snps,define.core))
  
  #plot results
  ggplot(x, aes(x=define.core,y=num.snps)) + geom_line() + ylab('Number of SNPs') + xlab('Percentage site conservation')
}
plotSnpsToTree <- function(tree.file, outgroups=FALSE, window.size=10000, snp.table){
  #provide tree file, vector of outgroup names, window size
  #drop outgroup tips from tree
  tip.label.index <- c(grep(paste(outgroups, collapse='|'),(tree.file$tip.label)))
  ingroup.tree<-drop.tip(tree.file, tree.file$tip.label[tip.label.index])
  recombination.density <- getRecombHeatmap(snp.table, ref="Ref", w=window.size)
  plotTree(tree=ingroup.tree, heatmapData=recombination.density,heatmap.colours=colorRampPalette(c("white","orange","red"),space="rgb")(100), colLabelCex=0.0001)
  
}
writeCoverageGenes <- function(coverage.table, coverage.level = 0.95, strain.percentage = 0.95){
  gene.totals <-apply(coverage.table, 1, function(x){sum(x>=(coverage.level*100))})
  x = strain.percentage*ncol(coverage.table)
  core = c(sum(gene.totals >= x))
  pick.genename = rownames(coverage.table)[which((gene.totals) >= x)]
  return(pick.genename)
}
